# Performance budget gate

Full reference: `performance-budget.md`. Budgets are enforced by
`npm run check:budgets` (runs automatically before every deploy). **Fast AND
visually premium — byte savings never justify degraded imagery.**

## Images — pipeline only, no exceptions

- Never drop a raw export into `src/assets/`. Full-res masters go in
  `assets-src/`; add a manifest entry in `scripts/optimize-images.mjs`
  (target width ≈ 2× largest rendered CSS px), then run
  `npm run optimize:images`.
- Never import from `assets-src/` in app code.
- **Visual quality gate is mandatory:** after regenerating, compare the
  rendered surface before/after at 1× and 2× (alpha edges, gradient banding,
  fine linework). If it fails, raise the width/quality in the manifest and
  re-run — do not ship the failure and do not skip the check.
- Budgets: single image ≤ 200 KB; total `src/assets/` ≤ 1,300 KB.

## JS — keep the split intact

- **Pages are lazy by default.** New pages go in the lazy `ActivePage` switch
  in `src/AuthedApp.tsx` via `React.lazy`. Home stays eager.
- **The signed-out path stays light.** Never import the app shell, pages,
  forge/watchlist/weather modules, or other heavy components from
  `src/App.tsx`, `LoginScreen`, `Onboarding`, or anything else that runs
  before sign-in.
- **Big secondary UI loads on open:** modals/panels over ~300 lines that are
  not visible on first render load via `React.lazy` (pattern: the forge table
  modals in `StrategyForgePanel`).
- New dependencies over ~30 KB gzip need a vendor-group decision in
  `vite.config.ts` and a budget check before landing.
- Budgets (gzip): entry chunk ≤ 80 KB; any chunk ≤ 100 KB.

## When a budget fails

Fix the regression (pipeline / splitting) — do not raise the number. If a
budget genuinely must grow (e.g. approved new artwork), update
`performance-budget.md` in the same change with the reason.

## QA before claiming done

Any change touching assets or the loading path: `npm run typecheck`,
`npm run build`, `npm run check:budgets`, plus the functional smoke and
locked-surface QA (`.cursor/rules/locked-surface-qa.mdc`).
